cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.MM 

The paper deals with computer vision and machine learning techniques applied to biomedical imaging. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses active learning and transfer learning, which are subfields of machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. Additionally, the paper involves decision-making processes, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses information retrieval and image analysis, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
